    authors: '<span class="font-bold text-black">Jason Lau</span> advised by Jason Cong'
    venue: "Ph.D. Dissertation, University of California, Los Angeles"
    abstract: "We introduce Heterosys, an end-to-end framework designed to bridge the gap between high-level software and efficient FPGA implementation. By decoupling algorithmic descriptions from underlying hardware, Heterosys utilizes three core components—HeteroRefactor for automated refactoring and selective offloading, Adroit for frequency-driven architectural optimization, and RapidIR for high-level physical synthesis and floorplanning. Our research demonstrates frequency improvements of 30% to over 100%, resource reductions up to 90%, and a 51% decrease in manual code effort, significantly lowering the barrier to entry for heterogeneous computing."
  - pdf: "research-papers/10.1145-3609335.pdf"
