    venue: "TRETS '23 - ACM Transactions on Reconfigurable Technology and Systems, Volume 16, Issue 4, Article No. 63, Pages 1 - 31"
    year: "2023"
    abstract: "We propose TAPA, an end-to-end framework for compiling C++ task-parallel programs into high-frequency FPGA accelerators. By utilizing flexible communication APIs and coarse-grained floorplanning during compilation, TAPA enables accurate pipelining of critical paths and optimizes designs for HBM-based FPGAs. Experimental results across 43 designs demonstrate a 102% average frequency improvement, including successful implementation of previously unroutable designs with minimal resource impact."
